  <FeatureBlock
    kicker="01 · ORCHESTRATION HUB"
    heading="The control room for multi-environment agent work"
    body="Codebolt Editor sits on top of the same server runtime used by CLI, cloud, and headless deployments. The editor becomes the human-facing control plane for agent runs that may execute locally, in Docker, in cloud sandboxes, on remote servers, or across provider-backed environments. You can monitor the run, inspect artifacts, review changes, and keep coordination state in one place."
    cta={{"label":"Read multi-environment docs","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/04_build-on-codebolt/08a_multi-environment-orchestration/01_overview"}}
    diagram="Codebolt Editor
    │
    ▼
Codebolt Server Runtime
    ├─ local laptop
    ├─ Docker / worktree
    ├─ E2B / Daytona
    ├─ remote Codebolt server
    └─ fleet environments

server remains the control plane
editor remains the operator surface
"
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    kicker="02 · EXTENSIBLE EDITOR"
    heading="Agents and plugins can extend the interface at runtime"
    body="The editor is an application host. Plugins can add panels, commands, provider integrations, and backend behavior. Agents can open dynamic panels for reviews, dashboards, forms, status views, approvals, or domain-specific workflows. The UI is not fixed to a single sidebar or chat panel; it can change with the task."
    cta={{"label":"Explore dynamic panels","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/04_build-on-codebolt/04_custom-uis/05_dynamic-panels"}}
    reverse={true}
    diagram="plugin backend
    │
    ├─ commands
    ├─ providers
    ├─ hooks
    └─ dynamic panel
           ▲
           │ messages / fetch / events
           ▼
editor UI panel inside Codebolt

agents can open, update, wait on,
and close panels during a run
"
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    kicker="03 · CODEBOLT-NATIVE APPS"
    heading="Run full application experiences on the engine"
    body="The biggest shift is that Codebolt Editor is not only where you write applications. It is also where Codebolt-native applications can run. A plugin can act as the backend, a dynamic panel can act as the frontend, and the Codebolt engine provides agents, tools, memory, events, project state, and execution. This is closer to cloud-native applications than a normal extension model: the app is designed around the runtime, not just hosted beside it."
    cta={{"label":"Read custom agentic apps","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/04_build-on-codebolt/04b_custom-agentic-applications/01_overview"}}
    diagram="Codebolt-native application
    │
    ├─ dynamic panel frontend
    ├─ plugin backend
    ├─ agent workflows
    ├─ tools + MCP + providers
    ├─ memory + event history
    └─ project / task state

runs inside the editor runtime
without requiring a separate server
"
  />
  <BentoGrid
    kicker="DEVELOPMENT LIFECYCLE"
    heading="Manage the full software lifecycle in one workspace"
    description="Codebolt Editor connects planning, implementation, agent management, evaluation, optimization, and delivery instead of scattering them across disconnected tools."
    columns={3}
    gap="none"
    items={[{"title":"Plan the work","tag":"Roadmap","description":"Capture product phases, features, specs, UI flows, and requirement plans as project files that agents can read before acting.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/06_planning/01_overview"},{"title":"Break it into execution","tag":"Action Plan","description":"Create structured action plans with tasks, dependencies, parallel groups, and progress that agents can update while they work.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/06_planning/06_action-plan"},{"title":"Track tasks on Kanban","tag":"Tasks","description":"Manage standalone tasks, subtasks, statuses, and kanban columns alongside the codebase and agent message history.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/06_planning/07_tasks"},{"title":"Develop with agents","tag":"Build","description":"Run coding agents against the project context, inspect file edits, review checkpoints, and keep human control over the work.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/04_agents/03_running-agents"},{"title":"Manage agent portfolios","tag":"Agents","description":"Use built-in agents, remixes, custom agents, remote agents, and specialized teams without leaving the editor surface.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/04_agents/06_agent-portfolios"},{"title":"Evaluate and optimize","tag":"Quality","description":"Define eval tasks, score outputs, compare runs, and run optimization loops that improve agents over iterations.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/05e_eval-and-optimization/01_overview"},{"title":"Observe every run","tag":"Trace","description":"Use debug panels, AI call inspection, console streams, and narrative graphs to see why an agent made each decision.","href":"https://docs.codebolt.ai/docs/02_using-codebolt/05c_agent-observability/01_overview","span":2,"visual":"roadmap -> spec -> action plan -> task\n     │         │          │         │\n     └──────── agents read/update ─┘\n\nrun -> logs -> trace -> eval -> optimize\n"},{"title":"Ship through the same runtime","tag":"Runtime","description":"Move from editor work to CLI, cloud, remote environments, or Codebolt-native application surfaces without changing the underlying engine.","href":"/engine"}]}
